                                    <!-- FAQ Section for AEO -->
                                    <div class="faq-section" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                                        <h3>How much does it cost to develop an app in the UK in 2026?</h3>
                                        <p>London tier-1 agencies charge GBP 120k-350k for an MVP. Manchester, Bristol and Leeds studios are 30-40% cheaper. Indian partners deliver the same scope for GBP 18k-55k including SCC-compliant data flows.</p>
                                        <h3>Is it GDPR-compliant to use an Indian app development company?</h3>
                                        <p>Yes. UK ICO recognises Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) for India transfers. Production data stays in UK/EU AWS regions; Indian engineers access via VPN + IAM least-privilege. Setup adds 2-3 days at project kick-off.</p>
                                        <h3>Which is the best app development company in London?</h3>
                                        <p>London tier-1 agencies include Cyber-Duck, Apadmi, Glance, ustwo and Brightec. They're excellent for FCA-regulated fintech, NHS workflows and brand-driven apps. For consumer marketplaces, SaaS and B2B apps the math favours offshore.</p>
                                        <h3>How do I manage time zones with an Indian app dev partner from the UK?</h3>
                                        <p>Indian working hours overlap UK working hours from ~1pm IST to 9pm IST (8:30am to 4:30pm UK). Daily standup at 1pm IST and weekly demo at 4pm IST gives you 4 working hours of overlap, which is plenty.</p>
                                        <h3>Can an Indian agency build an FCA-regulated fintech app for a UK client?</h3>
                                        <p>Yes for the build, but FCA-licensed entity, compliance-officer signoff and KYC integration must remain UK-side. We typically partner with the client's UK compliance team and own only the engineering stack. Several of our 2025 UK clients run this model.</p>
